<subSubSection id="A415A2FAA4874708B81CAF8B028A7885" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FD2AEE1C740284F65961AE3FFF89407B" pageNumber="23">
Diagnosis. A species of 
<taxonomicName id="7673B2E2049DA4D5E3ED3F733ACE61A1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:555B344D-5775-4AF5-A583-0AE42162235B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara Zugmayer 1911:12" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachycara</taxonomicName>
as defined by Anderson (1989, 1994) with the following combination of characters: scales and ventral lateral line absent; caudal vertebrae 67-69; gill rakers on upper limb 1-2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4C6BC01DDD3110F009316CD93C3E8F53" type="description">
<paragraph id="8704E0074B7CE3F8BE3F1ACC43AF7A75" pageNumber="23">Description. Counts and measurements, holotype first followed in parentheses by range of variation in paratypes: vertebrae 25 + 67 = 92 (25-26 + 67-69 = 92-95); D 87 (87-90); A 67 (67-70); C 9 (8-9); P 18 (18); pelv. 2 (2); vomerine teeth 2 (2-3); palatine teeth 4 + 4 (4-6 + 3-5); gill rakers 1 + 14 (1-2 + 12-16 = 13-18); branchiostegal rays 6 (6); pseudobranch filaments 4 (4). Following measurements in percent SL: head length 17.8 (16.3-17.8); head width 10.9 (9.6-11.1); head depth 11.1 (8.8-10.7); pectoral fin length 10.9 (9.4-12.5); predorsal length 20.0 (18.5-23.9); preanal length 45.3 (44.8- 47.5); body depth 12.1 (10.6-12.3); gill slit length 6.5 (5.4-6.1); caudal fin length 7.1 (4.6-7.0). Following measurements in percent HL: head width 61.6 (55.1-67.5); head depth 62.3 (53.7-63.9); upper jaw length 56.1 (36.0-51.8); pectoral fin length 61.6 (57.4- 76.5); snout length 22.7 (20.8-24.4); eye diameter 17.9 (16.2-19.9); gill slit length 36.4 (33.2-36.6); interorbital width 9.3 (8.9-12.4); interpupillary width 29.1 (29.3-35.9); pelvic fin length 13.3 (10.8-17.6). Pectoral base/length ratio: 39.4 (36.7-50.2).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="776EDA751D6F2D4E350873887B50C569" pageNumber="24">Head ovoid in young, more dorsoventrally depressed in adult male holotype. Scales and epidermal prickles absent. Spectacle of eye circular or slightly ovoid. Gill slit extending ventrally to opposite fourth or fifth ventralmost pectoral ray. Lobe at dorsal margin of gill slit weak, not extending anteriorly one-quarter eye diameter. Pectoral fin origin below body midlne, insertion on abdomen; posterior margin of fin wedge-shaped; middle pectoral rays longest; ventralmost four thickened, tips very slightly exserted.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6201A05895FF1FE5D444D236E010211A" pageNumber="24">Mouth subterminal, slightly oblique, upper jaw extending to middle of eye or its posterior margin (holotype). Rear lobe of lower lip well developed in holotype. Oral valve very weakly developed, well separated from anterior margin of vomer. Jaw teeth small, conical; dentary with three irregular rows anteriorly, blending into single posterior row; premaxilla with two anterior rows, blending into single posterior row. Vomerine and palatine teeth relatively few; palatine teeth in short anterior patch.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9689D966255F8B34314CACE44F00019" pageNumber="24">
Cephalic lateralis system in primitive state for 
<taxonomicName id="0FFA6E349487A9BADD562BCC164C8CCD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:555B344D-5775-4AF5-A583-0AE42162235B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara Zugmayer 1911:12" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachycara</taxonomicName>
(Anderson 1989), with two postorbital pores (numbers one and four), two pairs of anterior supraorbitals (nasals), six suborbitals, eight preoperculomandibulars and no occipitals or interorbital. Body lateral line with complete mediolateral branch originating directly behind last postorbital pore (Fig. 3). Predorsal branch with 17-20 neuromasts running from above or just behind eye to dorsal fin origin. No ventral or dorsolateral branches, few neuromasts in these regions on body and tail.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="644B73D0E8B696A625AC16B6C21CCFBD" pageNumber="24">Dorsal fin origin associated with fourth vertebra, with no free pterygiophores anteriorly. Anal fin origin associated with ultimate precaudal or first caudal vertebrae, with two pterygiophores inserted anterior to haemal spine of first caudal vertebra. Last dorsal ray associated with fourth preural vertebra, last anal ray associated with second preural vertebra. Caudal fin with one epural, four upper and four lower hypural rays. Gill rakers short, triangular, dorsalmost three in holotype shallowly furcate; single gill raker on epibranchial in three specimens, two in MOVI 21035, directed anteroventrally. Pseudobranch filaments long, simple.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2DE8087ED9A5EFF90A3B8C7EEA2032E4" pageNumber="24">Color uniformly dark chocolate brown, unpaired fins black. Eye blue. Abdomen with bluish tinge.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6F544BE549C979D211180AADC50ACF26" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D22EC7BEC5C2CB42C172166C539530CA" pageNumber="24">
Distribution. Southern Brazil, from 
<normalizedToken id="529268A3A554533CDE62D25C4E918018" originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo to Rio Grande do Sul, in 788-910 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BEA988338FCBB00F487DFC41F2E73AFA" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7F70058528D626809B16EF84108FECC1" pageNumber="24">Etymology. From the Greek lepidotos, covered with scales, and the negative prefix referring to the species scaleless condition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5FB5A8F4EAD9456BDA2B8989017590F5" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4642504373AE0307C6150CD66D5B8E38" lastPageNumber="25" pageNumber="24">
Comparisons. 
<taxonomicName id="183FA007C8DDE0ADA9E06010FFA77642" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alepidotum">Pachycara alepidotum</taxonomicName>
is the second of 21 known species of the genus without scales, the other being 
<taxonomicName id="38CB37745849E244B95B45CD7429F7F0" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
(Anderson 1989; 
<normalizedToken id="5AC5A378BA4B663353E16A389FD7B064" originalValue="Møller">Moller</normalizedToken>
2003), suggesting possible relationship. However, the two differ in several trenchant features including the more numerous vertebrae in 
<taxonomicName id="99CA8E267A4A2AF0C0CA63895A76C839" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
(120-122 vs 92-94 in 
<taxonomicName id="0F67E77A6ABF0F1C3A9D02556E3E89D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alepidotum">P. alepidotum</taxonomicName>
), pelvic fin rays 3 in 
<taxonomicName id="5982047349B3593D5DF18EAAF2705DB5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
vs 2 in 
<taxonomicName id="C6F1F17ABAAC93FF50FACF07B5DDD9FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alepidotum">P. alepidotum</taxonomicName>
, smaller head (length 11.4-12.0 in 
<taxonomicName id="1F487524DB114C1738DAF6259E64D1D4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
vs 16.3-17.8), more posterior dorsal fin origin (origin associated with vertebrae 7-8 in 
<taxonomicName id="3ADF803FF6033CAAD198D4932265922D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
vs 4), presence of the ventral branch of the lateral line system in 
<taxonomicName id="E00508421CA6B75B3DD3EB254125B84F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
vs its absence, and presence of an interorbital pore in 
<taxonomicName id="9A6D88FEA7E054D963243B3D9F264FA8" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
vs its absence. In addition, the habitats of 
<taxonomicName id="81C9AAB6E8903B116837F1E0AB76239F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:230F16F4-36D7-4F9D-AC6A-3C952270A421" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara shcherbachevi Anderson 1989:233" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shcherbachevi">P. shcherbachevi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="249FC97A8B3285ED299A4AA5F2F27281" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alepidotum">P. alepidotum</taxonomicName>
are different, the former is an Indian Ocean abyssal species, taken at 2600-3190 m, while the latter is an upper bathyal (788-807 m) Atlantic species. On the basis of its low vertebral counts, two pelvic fin rays and lack of ventral lateral line, 
<taxonomicName id="0C4F5AE173F99FA6BA38477306766E7B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05AB8F03-EC44-49D5-89B9-79238CF1A3E0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara rimae Anderson 1989:235" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rimae">P. rimae Anderson</taxonomicName>
, an eastern Pacific abyssal species, seems close to 
<taxonomicName id="8F4C6F18186395AE44941A1C990D39AC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alepidotum">P. alepidotum</taxonomicName>
, but it differs in the presence of scales, its fewer branchiostegal rays (4-5 in 
<taxonomicName id="E68ACA379B39B728E1AB5CBCBB074A4D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05AB8F03-EC44-49D5-89B9-79238CF1A3E0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara rimae Anderson 1989:235" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rimae">P. rimae</taxonomicName>
vs 6), more posterior dorsal fin origin(associated with vertebra 8 in 
<taxonomicName id="BB2452FE300609FD3A937601571363EB" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05AB8F03-EC44-49D5-89B9-79238CF1A3E0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara rimae Anderson 1989:235" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rimae">P. rimae</taxonomicName>
vs. 4), fewer pectoral fin rays (15 in 
<taxonomicName id="A12DD3D68B06637C09CDC633563C92B2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05AB8F03-EC44-49D5-89B9-79238CF1A3E0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara rimae Anderson 1989:235" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rimae">P. rimae</taxonomicName>
vs 18) and lack of a pseudobranch. Other bathyal southeastern Pacific (i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="34BF4B2C627F3194D1477A1C0FE6D5D1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EB4BEA68-DB42-4604-9638-2DC5CBB7849C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara mesoporum Anderson 1989:237" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mesoporum">P. mesoporum Anderson</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CE374823469C419C5A1520C4EABE65EF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CABCFBEE-9A26-413B-B165-8E57544ECC5C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara pammelas Anderson 1989:239" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pammelas">P. pammelas Anderson</taxonomicName>
) or eastern Atlantic (
<taxonomicName id="02A6109354AE11BAD2DC60F65395C4B5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassiceps">P. crassiceps Roule</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="657A8D638AE979CEA1F56BAA6F3A026D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B3D8A4C7-9A2D-4685-B753-B81CE8DCD188" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara crossacanthum Anderson 1989:230" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crossacanthum">P. crossacanthum Anderson</taxonomicName>
) species do not seem close to 
<taxonomicName id="40593A32C196B903404008332C44E6B0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alepidotum">P. alepidotum</taxonomicName>
on the basis of their complete squamation, higher vertebral counts and more complex lateral line systems. Thus the relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="362A95568EB334E1B1AC574A99CBE932" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alepidotum">P. alepidotum</taxonomicName>
are presently unclear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="065ECD2F990B77067073A9ECA81C2796" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="E561A7CF1FC43664E00B090AB860C55E" pageNumber="25">
Remarks. The single trawl-caught specimen (MNRJ 27754) was taken in a Great Opening Vertical (GOV) net, mouth size measuring 36 x 47 m. The bottom temperature at 900 m was 3.4°C. The trap-caught specimens were collected from galvanized circular crab pots baited with fish. The benthic fauna was diverse in deep-sea corals, echinoderms, mollusks and crustaceans. Fishes observed at and near the trap locations were hag fish (
<taxonomicName id="1F49E1F1BB5A791A9CCB4B0BA03162EF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9B8E7280-97CE-4E60-B8C2-5879C953EECF" class="Myxini" family="Myxinidae" genus="Eptatretus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Eptatretus menezesi Mincarone 2000:816" order="Myxiniformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menezesi">Eptatretus menezesi Mincarone</taxonomicName>
), sharpnose sevengill shark (
<taxonomicName id="F9AE824F9D161BE13D41D42C062C98A2" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Hexanchidae" genus="Heptranchias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hexanchiformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="perlo">Heptranchias perlo (Bonnaterre)</taxonomicName>
, freckled catshark (
<taxonomicName id="09C5DE3BD1F24C0C5A405EA43C6CA2F2" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Scyliorhinidae" genus="Scyliorhinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="haeckelii">Scyliorhinus haeckelii (Miranda Ribeiro)</taxonomicName>
, dogfish (
<taxonomicName id="739C4C9F4DF9C11AF2A267AAFE08ACB9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:27C908C9-6E54-4E19-AF92-7635023DAAF6" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Squalidae" genus="Squalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Squalus Linnaeus 1758:233" order="Squaliformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Squalus</taxonomicName>
sp.), an undescribed 
<taxonomicName id="C79FC443C511C2DD7FB91E4CB4766480" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:074EEEEA-D430-4519-9BA3-F4C7E1329D80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Congridae" genus="Conger" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Conger Klein 1775:22" order="Anguilliformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Conger</taxonomicName>
, dragonfish (
<taxonomicName id="733DE26C9642493C4F78F11029E8C9E6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CCD33FB1-B7B2-4F64-8003-008957F60575" class="Actinopterygii" family="Stomiidae" genus="Idiacanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Idiacanthus atlanticus Brauer 1906:62" order="Stomiiformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atlanticus">Idiacanthus atlanticus Brauer</taxonomicName>
), Marini’s grenadier (
<taxonomicName id="F9D116D14E6BC27AF9501778CDA1601B" authority="Giorna, 1809" authorityName="Giorna" authorityYear="1809" class="Teleostei" family="Macrouridae" genus="Caelorinchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marinii">Caelorinchus marinii Hubbs</taxonomicName>
), Atlantic grenadier (
<taxonomicName id="6AB5F1DD87704D2102C3B450EF38326B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aequalis">
Nezumia aequalis (
<normalizedToken id="C98BD25228D5727608A36DD395D457E4" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
)
</taxonomicName>
, common fangtooth (
<taxonomicName id="5DC06F304ED8AE85020E98A4D853E305" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anoplogastridae" genus="Anoplogaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beryciformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cornuta">Anoplogaster cornuta (Valenciennes)</taxonomicName>
, banded yellowfish (
<taxonomicName id="1E3AFAFB5CF152C37219529BDB726A90" class="Actinopterygii" family="Centriscidae" genus="Centriscops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Syngnathiformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="humerosus">Centriscops humerosus (Richardson)</taxonomicName>
, sculpin (
<taxonomicName id="AE42DD5200D190419D302A65DAE19862" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:11139399-F61F-4E22-B065-AA480F7FCE31" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psychrolutidae" genus="Cottunculus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cottunculus granulosus Karrer 1968:560" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="granulosus">Cottunculus granulosus Karrer</taxonomicName>
), tilefish (
<taxonomicName id="A09A3FDA2AD3B671172B30F9E2496B67" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EDDF6CDE-77E7-4139-B3AE-D13DF4D7505D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Lopholatilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Lopholatilus villarii Miranda-Ribeiro 1915:Malacanthidae p. 8" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="villarii">Lopholatilus villarii Miranda Ribeiro</taxonomicName>
), and corocoro grunt (
<taxonomicName id="F5CEEB7B40DCF3863F1991E31B4B19A1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Orthopristis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">Orthopristis ruber (Cuvier)</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
